12:21.420 --> 12:24.060
a commentary on science fiction and fantasy.

12:26.760 --> 12:28.520
And here are your hosts.

12:32.780 --> 12:34.100
This is Daryl Lane.

12:34.200 --> 12:34.900
And Bill Vernon.

12:35.400 --> 12:39.020
Marion Zimmer Bradley's Darkover stories are based on one overall conflict,

12:39.020 --> 12:43.720
the technological might of Earth versus the telepathic powers of the inhabitants of Darkover.

12:43.860 --> 12:51.280
The planet Darkover, circling a blood-red sun, contains valuable crystals which greatly magnify and concentrate telepathic ability.

12:51.280 --> 12:54.320
These crystals are the basis of the Darkover civilization.

12:54.820 --> 12:59.100
Earth wants access to the crystals, and it wants Darkover as part of its interstellar empire.

12:59.360 --> 13:00.720
But the Darkover's resist.

13:01.040 --> 13:04.780
The conflict never really breaks into a full-scale interplanetary war,

13:04.980 --> 13:09.580
but the tension leads to all sorts of intrigues, skirmishes, and spying activities.

13:10.220 --> 13:12.480
Relying on their mental powers is the Darkover's do.

13:12.740 --> 13:14.280
They've never developed a technology.

13:14.560 --> 13:18.440
In fact, they often seem anti-technological, though Bradley says this is not the case.

13:18.440 --> 13:26.720
I don't think so much anti-technological as thinking that perhaps there are better ways to do things than by technology.

13:27.040 --> 13:36.400
It isn't so much anti-technological as a concept that possibly the same kind of technology does not fit every planet,

13:36.620 --> 13:39.800
just as materialism does not fit every human mind,

13:39.920 --> 13:45.200
that there are different universes for different mental sets, as you said.

13:45.200 --> 13:50.020
I think I'm a very sort of alternative culture person myself,

13:50.480 --> 13:57.280
and from the time I was a child I have never liked the idea that everybody has to fit into the same lockstep

13:57.280 --> 14:00.060
and be, well, they now say be clones.

14:00.320 --> 14:06.380
My daughter calls the ordinary kids at school who never think of anything except football games clones.

14:07.000 --> 14:09.780
Well, I felt that way when I was a youngster,

14:09.840 --> 14:14.840
and so I suppose the idea of leaving open options and choices for everybody

14:14.840 --> 14:17.740
so they can find the kind of lifestyle that suits them best

14:17.740 --> 14:22.560
instead of blamly assuming that everybody has to belong to the same lifestyle.

14:22.560 --> 14:25.640
That was something that I felt very strongly about when I was a kid,

14:25.640 --> 14:28.680
and I feel even more strongly about than I did when I was 15.

14:29.800 --> 14:34.560
Bradley seems to be fairly even-handed in presenting the conflict between Darkover and Earth,

14:34.700 --> 14:39.860
but she also has sympathy for Darkover's position and even seems to admire its way of life.

14:39.860 --> 14:45.060
We asked her if it would be fair to say that she tends to be slightly on the side of non-technological Darkover.

14:45.680 --> 14:49.400
No, I would not. My very life is dependent on technology.

14:49.980 --> 14:54.800
I am myself a diabetic and dependent upon medical preparations,

14:54.840 --> 14:59.060
which are very difficult to get in an anti-techno or a non-technological culture.

14:59.060 --> 15:08.760
It is simply that I do what you call an even-handed job because, well, my husband says it's because I'm a Gemini,

15:08.760 --> 15:13.180
and it's true that I am cursed with seeing two sides of everything.

15:13.460 --> 15:18.040
When I was a kid and reading in school about what a terrible person Benedict Arnold was,

15:18.040 --> 15:20.800
I still realized that to the British he was a hero,

15:20.800 --> 15:23.800
and it suddenly occurred to me that the villain is always,

15:24.080 --> 15:29.720
except for real criminals like mass murderers, rapists, that sort of thing,

15:29.880 --> 15:35.240
almost every, quote, villain, unquote, is just the victim of a political conflict.

15:35.540 --> 15:37.240
He's the hero of the other side.

15:38.380 --> 15:42.660
One thing, though, that Bradley admires in the Darkover society is the compact.

15:43.080 --> 15:47.280
The compact outlaws guns, explosives, or energy weapons of any kind.

15:47.280 --> 15:51.340
Any fighting must be done with swords, knives, bows and arrows, and so forth.

15:52.200 --> 15:55.100
In this day and age with nuclear weapons every place,

15:55.240 --> 15:58.600
I think every human being has to be in sympathy with the compact,

15:58.860 --> 16:01.000
or if they aren't, there's something wrong with their brains.

16:01.600 --> 16:05.260
At least under the compact, if you have only a sword or a knife,

16:05.280 --> 16:09.120
you can do only one person's amount of damage.

16:09.380 --> 16:13.660
I suppose it's my emotional reaction to the fact that when I was 15 years old,

16:13.660 --> 16:16.900
it became possible to wipe out all human life on Earth

16:16.900 --> 16:20.620
if one paranoid politician presses the wrong button.

16:21.740 --> 16:24.020
And I think maybe that's too much power

16:24.020 --> 16:29.440
and would like to see power back in the hands of individuals over their own lives.

16:30.320 --> 16:33.620
I don't like the idea that we are all, you might say,

16:33.760 --> 16:38.180
hostages in a monstrous political and ideological conflict.

16:38.960 --> 16:42.260
I can't believe that God is on one side

16:42.940 --> 16:45.440
and that on the other there is only the devil.

